The fluorescence lifetime decay kinetics for donor fluorophore, acceptor alone or in the form of N-CDots/AuNCs were determined by fitting the data to a double exponential decay. For N-CDots/AuNCs, strong quenching of the donor results in a shortening of the donor lifetime (Table 1
                         and Fig. 3
                        ). These measurements can be used to determine the FRET efficiency, and the results are shown in Table 1.
